FEATURED WORKS

TPSY - Beer Buddy (Client)

TPSY Client Repo on Github [ https://github.com/Sean-Drew/TPSY-client ] In the past few years the craft beer scene has exploded. Whenever I go to a packie (liquor store for non-Mass folks) I'm always seeing new beers with sharp packaging and impressive labels drawing me over, but it's just not realistic to buy the whole store! Sometimes I feel like I can't keep track of the beers I've already tried, the ones I want to try, and whether I liked them or not. Enter TPSY. Designed on a jQuery/Express platform, TPSY is a web application for beer aficionados to keep track of the beers they've tried, and to keep notes on them.

Envoy (Client)

Envoy Client Repo on Github [ https://github.com/Sean-Drew/group-project-client ] I know what you're thinking - "there's just not enough places for me to post pictures of my dog online". Well that's what I'm thinking at least. Look no further! Now there's at least 1 more place where you can share some thoughts, photos, ask questions and comment on whatever else is on the website, with Envoy! The technologies that went into Envoy include Express and React.

Tic-Tac-Toe Game (Client)

Tic-Tac-Toe Game Client Repo on Github [ https://github.com/Sean-Drew/group-project-client ] That's right, a game of tic-tac-toe. My 'hello world' project, the first of the first, from no coding experience to this in a couple of weeks. The only thing special about this tic-tac-toe game is that it's where it all started, my foray into the world of coding. I keep this project around and refuse to tinker with it so I can always look back to see where I started and measure my growth over time. It's a reminder that you can accomplish anything you set your mind to.

ABOUT ME

...as a PERSON I describe myself as a hobbyist. I like to learn how to do things, how to make things and find out how things work. Every day is an opportunity to learn something new. I'm Massachusetts born & raised, currently residing in northern MA near the NH border with my wife and 2 dogs. You can normally find me buried in one of my hobbies, playing video games, kayaking, catching up on some tv shows, or out on a nice relaxing motorcycle ride.

...as a PROFESSIONAL It's all in the details, so to make sure the details are well kept I take a 'measure twice, cut once' mindset. Working alone, as a team or somewhere in-between, it's always important to be sensible and organized. You don't need a reason to keep improving on yourself professionally so I'm keen on learning new things, or even new ways of doing things I'm already familiar with.
